"""
PrismResonance — Biologically-Inspired Dynamic Memory Layer for RAG & Multi-Agent Systems

Two-level hierarchical memory middleware that converts static embeddings into
context-aware, state-driven wave packets.  Sits as a non-destructive sidecar
above any read-only vector database.

Quick start
-----------
::

    import numpy as np
    from prismresonance import PrismResonance
    from prismresonance.frequency import FrequencyFamily

    # Build (compiles ONNX graph on first run)
    prism = PrismResonance.create(embedding_dim=384)

    # Ingest
    amplitude = np.random.randn(384).astype(np.float32)
    amplitude /= np.linalg.norm(amplitude)
    prism.ingest("chunk_001", amplitude, FrequencyFamily.EMERGENCY)

    # Query
    q_amp = np.random.randn(384).astype(np.float32)
    q_amp /= np.linalg.norm(q_amp)
    results = prism.query(q_amp, FrequencyFamily.EMERGENCY,
                          ["chunk_001"], np.stack([amplitude]))

    # Inspect indexes
    recent  = prism.most_recent(n=5)
    related = prism.most_related("chunk_001", n=5)

    # Consolidate
    prism.sleep()
    prism.shutdown()

License
-------
Core library: MIT (open source)
Enterprise features: commercial — see https://prismresonance.insightits.com
"""

